    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Dungeoneer's Handbook pg. 25</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> <img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/> 70 gp (common), <img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/> 820 gp (mithral); <strong>Weight</strong> 3 lbs. (common), 1 1/2 lbs. (mithral)</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2><p>These long-reaching extenders can be attached to or detached from thieves' tools as a standard action, allowing the user to make Disable Device checks on devices in any space he could reach with a reach weapon. High-quality mirrors on the shafts let him see what he's doing, but he takes a -4 penalty on Disable Device checks when working on a device more than 5 feet away.</p>",
